  sections={sections}
>
  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section id="introduction">
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> (ABN: 74 649 452 077) is committed to protecting your privacy and handling your personal information responsibly. This <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> explains how we collect, use, disclose, store, and protect your <strong>personal information</strong> in accordance with the <strong>Australian Privacy Principles (APPs)</strong> under the <strong>Privacy Act 1988 (Cth)</strong>.</p>

    <p>As an Australian-based <strong>digital marketing agency</strong>, we understand the importance of <strong>data protection</strong> and <strong>privacy compliance</strong>. This policy applies to all personal information collected through our website, email communications, contact forms, and business interactions.</p>

    <p>By using our services or providing us with personal information, you consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described in this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong>.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Information We Collect -->
  <section id="information-we-collect">
    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> collects various types of <strong>personal information</strong> necessary to provide our <strong>digital marketing services</strong> and maintain business operations.</p>

    <h3>2.1 Personal Information</h3>
    <p>We may collect the following types of personal information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact Details:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, business address</li>
      <li><strong>Business Information:</strong> Company name, ABN/ACN, industry, job title</li>
      <li><strong>Communication Records:</strong> Correspondence via email, contact forms, phone calls</li>
      <li><strong>Financial Information:</strong> Payment details, billing address, invoice history</li>
      <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device information, operating system</li>
      <li><strong>Website Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on site, referral sources, click behavior</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing Preferences:</strong> Communication preferences, subscription status, engagement history</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2.2 Sensitive Information</h3>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> does not intentionally collect <strong>sensitive information</strong> (such as health information, racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs, or criminal records) unless required for specific business purposes and with your explicit consent.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- How We Collect -->
  <section id="how-we-collect">
    <h2>3. How We Collect Personal Information</h2>
    <p>We collect <strong>personal information</strong> through various methods:</p>

    <h3>3.1 Direct Collection</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> When you submit inquiries through our website contact forms</li>
      <li><strong>Email Communications:</strong> When you email us directly or respond to our emails</li>
      <li><strong>Phone Conversations:</strong> During business calls and consultations</li>
      <li><strong>Service Agreements:</strong> When you engage our digital marketing services</li>
      <li><strong>Events and Networking:</strong> At industry events, conferences, or business meetings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.2 Automated Collection</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Website Analytics:</strong> Through Google Analytics and similar tracking technologies</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Browser cookies that track website usage (see our <a href="/legal/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Server Logs:</strong> Automatically recorded when you visit our website</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3.3 Third-Party Sources</h3>
    <p>We may collect information from publicly available sources, business directories, social media platforms (LinkedIn, Facebook), or trusted third-party service providers.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- How We Use -->
  <section id="how-we-use">
    <h2>4. How We Use Your Personal Information</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> uses your <strong>personal information</strong> for the following purposes:</p>

    <h3>4.1 Service Delivery</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Providing <strong>digital marketing services</strong> including SEO, content marketing, PPC, social media management</li>
      <li>Managing client accounts and project delivery</li>
      <li>Communicating about service updates, campaigns, and performance reports</li>
      <li>Processing payments and maintaining financial records</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.2 Business Operations</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Responding to inquiries and providing customer support</li>
      <li>Improving our website, services, and user experience</li>
      <li>Conducting market research and business analysis</li>
      <li>Managing relationships with clients and partners</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.3 Marketing and Communications</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Sending promotional emails about our services (with your consent)</li>
      <li>Sharing industry insights, blog updates, and marketing resources</li>
      <li>Conducting email marketing campaigns and newsletters</li>
      <li>Advertising through digital channels (Google Ads, social media)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4.4 Legal and Compliance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Complying with legal obligations under Australian law</li>
      <li>Enforcing our <a href="/legal/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
      <li>Protecting our rights, property, and safety</li>
      <li>Resolving disputes and preventing fraud</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Disclosure -->
  <section id="disclosure">
    <h2>5. Disclosure of Personal Information</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> may disclose your <strong>personal information</strong> to third parties in the following circumstances:</p>

    <h3>5.1 Service Providers</h3>
    <p>We engage trusted third-party service providers to support our business operations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloud Hosting Providers:</strong> For website hosting and data storage</li>
      <li><strong>Email Marketing Platforms:</strong> For managing email campaigns and communications</li>
      <li><strong>Payment Processors:</strong> For processing invoices and payments securely</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics Tools:</strong> Google Analytics, heatmap tools, and tracking services</li>
      <li><strong>CRM Systems:</strong> Customer relationship management platforms</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing Platforms:</strong> Google Ads, Facebook Ads, LinkedIn Advertising</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
    <p>We may disclose personal information when required by law, court order, subpoena, or to comply with legal processes. This includes disclosures to law enforcement agencies, regulatory bodies, or government authorities.</p>

    <h3>5.3 Business Transfers</h3>
    <p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, sale, or transfer of business assets, your personal information may be transferred to the new entity. We will notify you of any such change in ownership.</p>

    <h3>5.4 With Your Consent</h3>
    <p>We may disclose your information to other third parties with your explicit consent or at your direction.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Data Security -->
  <section id="data-security">
    <h2>6. Data Security and Storage</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> takes <strong>data security</strong> seriously and implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your <strong>personal information</strong> from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.</p>

    <h3>6.1 Security Measures</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> SSL/TLS encryption for data transmission</li>
      <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Restricted access to personal information on a need-to-know basis</li>
      <li><strong>Secure Storage:</strong> Password-protected systems and encrypted databases</li>
      <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> Security patches and software updates</li>
      <li><strong>Employee Training:</strong> Staff training on privacy and data protection</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>6.2 Data Retention</h3>
    <p>We retain your <strong>personal information</strong> for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong>, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. Retention periods vary depending on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Active client relationships and ongoing service delivery</li>
      <li>Legal and regulatory requirements (typically 7 years for financial records)</li>
      <li>Legitimate business interests and record-keeping</li>
    </ul>

    <p>When personal information is no longer required, we will securely delete or anonymize it.</p>

    <h3>6.3 Data Breach Response</h3>
    <p>In the unlikely event of a <strong>data breach</strong> that poses a risk of serious harm, we will notify affected individuals and the <strong>Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)</strong> in accordance with the <strong>Notifiable Data Breaches (NDB) scheme</strong> under the Privacy Act 1988.</p>
  </section>

