    <h3>7.1 Types of Cookies</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Google Analytics to understand user behavior</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> For targeted advertising and remarketing</li>
      <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> To remember your settings and preferences</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>7.2 Google Analytics</h3>
    <p>We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> to collect information about website traffic, user behavior, and demographics. This data helps us improve our website and services. Google Analytics may collect your <strong>IP address</strong>, device information, and browsing patterns. You can opt out of Google Analytics by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>

    <h3>7.3 Managing Cookies</h3>
    <p>You can control and manage cookies through your browser settings. However, disabling cookies may affect website functionality and your user experience.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Your Rights -->
  <section id="your-rights">
    <h2>8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
    <p>Under the <strong>Australian Privacy Principles (APPs)</strong> and the <strong>Privacy Act 1988</strong>, you have the following rights regarding your <strong>personal information</strong>:</p>

    <h3>8.1 Right to Access</h3>
    <p>You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you. We will provide access unless there is a legal reason to deny your request.</p>

    <h3>8.2 Right to Correction</h3>
    <p>You can request correction of inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated personal information. We will take reasonable steps to correct your information.</p>

    <h3>8.3 Right to Opt-Out</h3>
    <p>You can opt out of receiving <strong>marketing communications</strong> at any time by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clicking the "unsubscribe" link in our emails</li>
      <li>Contacting us directly at privacy@growthexperts.com.au</li>
      <li>Updating your communication preferences in your account settings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>8.4 Right to Erasure</h3>
    <p>In certain circumstances, you may request deletion of your personal information. We will comply with your request unless we have a legitimate reason to retain the data (e.g., legal obligations, ongoing contracts).</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Access and Correction -->
  <section id="access-correction">
    <h2>9. Access and Correction</h2>
    <p>To access or correct your <strong>personal information</strong>, please contact us at:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@growthexperts.com.au</li>
      <li><strong>Subject Line:</strong> "Privacy Request - Access/Correction"</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We will respond to your request within <strong>30 days</strong>. There is no charge for requesting access to your personal information, but we may charge a reasonable fee for processing complex requests.</p>

    <p>To verify your identity, we may request additional information before processing your access or correction request.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Complaints -->
  <section id="complaints">
    <h2>10. Privacy Complaints</h2>
    <p>If you believe we have breached the <strong>Australian Privacy Principles</strong> or your privacy rights, you can lodge a complaint with <strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong>.</p>

    <h3>10.1 Internal Complaint Process</h3>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Submit Your Complaint:</strong> Email privacy@growthexperts.com.au with details of your concern</li>
      <li><strong>Investigation:</strong> We will investigate your complaint within 30 days</li>
      <li><strong>Response:</strong> We will provide a written response outlining our findings and any corrective actions</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>10.2 External Complaint to OAIC</h3>
    <p>If you are not satisfied with our response, you can lodge a complaint with the <strong>Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/">www.oaic.gov.au</a></li>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 1300 363 992</li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> enquiries@oaic.gov.au</li>
      <li><strong>Online Form:</strong> <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/privacy-complaints">OAIC Complaint Form</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>For more information about the <strong>Privacy Act 1988</strong>, visit: <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Details/C2021C00452">Privacy Act 1988 - Australian Legislation</a></p>
  </section>

  <!-- International Transfers -->
  <section id="international-transfers">
    <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>Some of our <strong>service providers</strong> and cloud hosting platforms may be located outside Australia, including the United States, Europe, and Asia. When we transfer your <strong>personal information</strong> overseas, we take reasonable steps to ensure:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The overseas recipient complies with the <strong>Australian Privacy Principles</strong></li>
      <li>Your information is protected through contractual agreements</li>
      <li>Adequate data protection measures are in place</li>
    </ul>

    <p>By using our services, you consent to the transfer of your personal information to overseas recipients for the purposes outlined in this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong>.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Children's Privacy -->
  <section id="children-privacy">
    <h2>12. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p><strong>Digital Growth Experts</strong> does not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under the age of 18. Our services are designed for businesses and professionals. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected information from a child, we will take steps to delete it promptly.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Changes -->
  <section id="changes">
    <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements, or business operations. The updated policy will be posted on this page with a revised "Last Updated" date.</p>

    <p>We encourage you to review this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> periodically to stay informed about how we protect your personal information. Continued use of our services after changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section id="contact">
    <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this <strong>Privacy Policy</strong> or our handling of your <strong>personal information</strong>, please contact us:</p>

